            <head xml:id="bHY6yh-d98385-Hd1e108">Rubrica 5</head>
            <head xml:id="bHY6yh-d98385-Hd1e111" type="question-title">De militia et officio et laudibus militum et sacramento eorum</head>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d98385-d1e114">
               De militia et officio 
               <lb ed="#O"/>et laudibus militum et sacramento eorum. 
               <lb ed="#O"/>Rubrica. 5.
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d98385-d1e121">
               <!--line bumps down-->
               <lb ed="#O"/><ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d98385-Rd1e118">UEgetius <!--line bumps up--> de re militari libro 2. titulo 5.</ref> <!--line bumps back down--> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d98385-Qd1e127">Iurant milites omnia 
               <lb ed="#O"/>se strenue facturos que pre<lb ed="#O" break="no"/>ceperit 
               imperator nunquam deserturos 
               <lb ed="#O"/>militiam nec mortem recusaturos 
               <lb ed="#O"/>pro re publica.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d98385-d1e139"> 
               ¶ <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d98385-Rd1e137">18. libro.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d98385-Qd1e141">In congruum 
               <lb ed="#O"/>uideretur imperatoris militem qui ueste 
               <pb ed="#O" n="207-r"/>
               <cb ed="#O" n="a"/>
               <lb ed="#O"/>et annona publica pasceretur uti<lb ed="#O" break="no"/>litatibus 
               uacare puatis.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d98385-d1e150"> 
               ¶ <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d98385-Rd1e150">33 titulo
               <lb ed="#O"/>et penultimo.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d98385-Qd1e152">Miles sacramento lectus ab exercitio 
               <lb ed="#O"/>armorum uel nouellus uel uetustus 
               <lb ed="#O"/>cesare non debet cui pugnandum est.
               <lb ed="#O"/>pro salute propria uel libertate communi.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d98385-d1e164"> 
               <lb ed="#O"/><ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d98385-Rd1e167">ref omitted</ref> ¶ <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d98385-Qd1e166">Publicis debent utilitatibus insudare 
               <lb ed="#O"/>qui nomen dedere militie. quid enim 
               <lb ed="#O"/>agat homo si professo desit officio</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d98385-d1e176"> 
               <lb ed="#O"/><ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d98385-Rd1e181">libro 3. titulo 3.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d98385-Qd1e178">Diuitiarum secura non est 
               <lb ed="#O"/>possessio nisi armorum defensione serue<lb ed="#O" break="no"/>tur.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d98385-d1e186"> 
               ¶ <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d98385-Rd1e193">10. titulo.</ref> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d98385-Qd1e188">Quis dubitat artem bel<lb ed="#O" break="no"/>licam 
               rebus omnibus esse potiorem
               <lb ed="#O"/>per quam libertas retinetur et dignitas 
               <lb ed="#O"/>prouincie propagatur conseruatur 
               <lb ed="#O"/>imperium.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d98385-d1e198">
               <!--line bumps down-->
               <lb ed="#O"/><ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d98385-Rd1e209">CAssio<!--line bumps up-->dorus epistolarum. libro i. epsitola 16.</ref> <!--line bumps back down--> <quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d98385-Qd1e202">Animus ipse in audaciam 
               <lb ed="#O"/>non potest esse pronus qui diuersa 
               <lb ed="#O"/>cura fuerit sollicitus hanc meri<lb ed="#O" break="no"/>to 
               expeditionem nominauere maiores
               <lb ed="#O"/>quia mens deuota preliis non dicitur 
               <lb ed="#O"/>aliis cogitationibus occupari. 
               <lb ed="#O"/>¶ Constat tempore necessitatis illum 
               <lb ed="#O"/>probari fortissimum uirum qui se per 
               <lb ed="#O"/>multa non distrahit.</quote>
            </p>
            <p xml:id="bHY6yh-d98385-d1e221"> 
               ¶ <ref xml:id="bHY6yh-d98385-Rd1e232">libro 11. epistola. 37.</ref> 
               <lb ed="#O"/><quote xml:id="bHY6yh-d98385-Qd1e223">Sub incerta uita militia est.</quote>
            </p>
